 BY AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI The All Progressives Congress in Ebonyi State has congratulated President Mohammadu Buhari over the successful convention of the party. The party’s state Chairman, Stanley Okoro-emegha, expressed the congratulatory message in a statement issued in Abakaliki, describing the exercise as being organised in accordance with democratic tenets. Okoro-emegha’s message read that “Sequel to the successful conduct of the National Convention of the All Progressives Congress, may I heartily appreciate our leader, President Muhammadu Buhari for allowing democratic tenets to guide the process. “A commensurate note of gratitude also goes to other national leaders of our party who shelved their differences in order to accommodate the interest of the party. “This note of appreciation cannot be complete without the mention of some other critical stakeholders who helped to midwife the transparent, credible, reliable and peaceful process such as the security personnel, the Independent National Electoral Commission, and the media. “Your diverse roles will ever remain indelible on the sands of time.” 